sent_ground <- read_tsv("sub_lexicon/sublex_1_0.csv", 
                        col_names = c("negation", "pos", "word", "polarity", "source") ) %>% 
  mutate(word = stringi::stri_trans_general(word,"Latin-ASCII")) %>% 
  mutate(word = iconv(word,to="UTF-8")) %>% 
  mutate(word = tolower(word)) %>% 
  mutate(word = str_replace_all(word, "_.*", "")) 

sent_data <- left_join(words, sent_ground, by = "word") %>% 
  select(-negation, pos, source) %>% 
  mutate(polarity = replace_na(polarity, "NEUTRAL"))

neg_counts <- sent_data %>% 
  filter(polarity == "NEG") %>% 
  group_by(id) %>% 
  count(polarity) 

neg_messages <- texts_fb %>% 
  inner_join(neg_counts, by = "id") %>% 
  arrange(desc(n))

top_neg_messages <- neg_messages %>% 
  top_n(100) %>% 
  select(polarity, n, message) 

top_neg_commie_messages <- neg_messages %>% 
  select(polarity, n, message) %>% 
  filter(str_detect(message, "komunis|socialis"))

More nuanced distribution of sentiment.


polarity_counts <- sent_data %>% 
  mutate(id = factor(id),
         polarity = factor(polarity)) %>% 
  select(id, polarity, type) %>% 
  group_by(id, type) %>% 
  count(polarity) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  spread(polarity, n) %>% 
  mutate(sentiment = case_when(
    POS == 0 & NEG == 0 ~ "neutral",
    POS > 0 & NEG == 0 ~ "positive",
    NEG > 0 & POS == 0 ~ "negative",
    NEG > POS ~ "negative mainly", # option
    POS > NEG ~ "positive mainly", # option
    POS == NEG & POS > 0 ~ "neutral-bipolar"#, # option
    # POS > 0 & NEG > 0 ~ "bipolar" # alternative
  ))

polarity_counts %>% 
  count(sentiment)

polarity_counts %>% 
  group_by(type) %>% 
  count(sentiment) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = type, y = n, fill = sentiment)) +
  geom_col(position = "fill") 

test <- polarity_counts %>% 
  mutate(sentiment = case_when(
    POS == 0 & NEG == 0 ~ "0",
    POS > 0 & NEG == 0 ~ "1",
    NEG > 0 & POS == 0 ~ "-1",
    NEG > POS ~ "-0.5", # option
    POS > NEG ~ "0.5", # option
    POS == NEG & POS > 0 ~ "0"#, # option
  )) %>% 
  mutate(sentiment = as.double(sentiment)) %>% 
  group_by(type) %>% 
  summarise(n = mean(sentiment))

get_tag <- function(x) {
  
tempfile_in <- tempfile() 
tempfile_out <- tempfile()
write(x, tempfile_in)
brace <- '"'
system(paste0("curl -F data=@", tempfile_in, " -F tokenizer= -F tagger= -F parser= http://lindat.mff.cuni.cz/services/udpipe/api/process | PYTHONIOENCODING=utf-8 python -c ", brace, "import sys,json; sys.stdout.write(json.load(sys.stdin)[\'result\'])", brace, " > ", tempfile_out))
system(paste0("curl -F data=@", tempfile_in, " -F tokenizer= -F tagger= -F parser= http://lindat.mff.cuni.cz/services/udpipe/api/process > ", tempfile_out))
result <- readLines(tempfile_out)
result <- gsub("# newdoc.*|# newpar.*|# text.*|# sent_id.*", "", result)
result <- result[result != ""]
y <- read_tsv(result, col_names = c(
  "word_id", "token", "lemma", "pos", "xpos", "desc_pos", "head", "deprel", "dep", "misc"),
  col_types = "iccccciccc")
}

                     x = x)
y <- as.data.frame(y)

                        col_names = c("negation", "pos", "word", "polarity", "source") ) %>% 
  mutate(word = stringi::stri_trans_general(word,"Latin-ASCII")) %>%

gold_test <- left_join(gold_df, sent_ground %>% select(word, polarity), by = "word") %>% 
  mutate(polarity = replace_na(polarity, "NEUTRAL")) %>% 
  group_by(id) %>% 
  count(polarity) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  spread(polarity, n, fill = "0") %>% 
  left_join(gold_df %>% select(id, gold_labels)) %>% 
  distinct() %>% 
  rename(Label = gold_labels) %>% 
  mutate(NEG = as.integer(NEG),
         POS = as.integer(POS),
         NEUTRAL = as.integer(NEUTRAL),
         Label = as.factor(Label)) %>% 
  group_by(id) %>% 
  mutate(No_words = sum(NEG, NEUTRAL, POS)) %>% 
  ungroup() 
  


indexes <- createDataPartition(gold_test$Label, times = 1,
                               p = 0.7, list = FALSE)

train <- gold_test[indexes,]
test <- gold_test[-indexes,]

cv.folds <- createMultiFolds(train$Label, k = 10, times = 3)

cv.cntrl <- trainControl(method = "repeatedcv", number = 10,
                         repeats = 3, index = cv.folds)

rpart.cv.4 <- train(Label ~ ., data = train[,-1], method = "naive_bayes", 
                    trControl = cv.cntrl)

yybaydata <- gold_test %>% mutate(NEG = as.integer(NEG),
         POS = as.integer(POS),
         NEUTRAL = as.integer(NEUTRAL),
         gold_labels = as.factor(gold_labels))


Naive_Bayes_Model <- naiveBayes(gold_labels ~., data = baydata[,-1])
